106 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MALL STORE ROBBED OF $100,000 IN JEWELRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A jewelry store in Northridge Fashion Center was burglarized of an estimated 
$100,000 worth of rings, watches, diamonds and other jewelry, Los Angeles 
police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
One or more burglars broke into Hudson-Goodman Jewelers shortly after 2 a.m. 
Thursday, Lt. Harvie Eubank said. 
</P>
<P>
A rear door of the store was pried open and a battery-operated alarm was 
deactivated, but investigators have not determined how the burglar or burglars 
entered the mall, Eubank said. 
</P>
<P>
Several glass display cases were smashed, and items were taken selectively, 
with the least valuable jewelry left behind, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The store opened about a week ago. 
</P>
