<P>
GRAFFITI GONE, SUBWAY CARS IN N.Y. START AFRESH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The last graffiti-covered subway train in New York City quietly went out of 
service Friday, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
All of the 6,245 subway cars have been replaced or gutted and rebuilt and 
scrubbed clean as a result of a five-year program that at its height used 1,000 
workers. 
</P>
<P>
Transit Authority spokesmen said that, if a car is marked up, it will be pulled 
out of service and cleaned within 24 hours before being allowed back on the 
tracks. 
