<P>
Metro; Part 2; Page 2; Column 4; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
134 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GUNMAN KILLS DRIVER AS HE GETS INTO VAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Atlantic Richfield refinery worker leaving his Carson home for work with a 
colleague was shot and killed Friday by a gunman apparently hiding in the back 
of his van, sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was not immediately identified. 
</P>
<P>
After shooting the 55-year-old man in the chest, the gunman also fired at the 
man's co-worker, who was sitting in the passenger seat of the van, but he 
missed, Deputy Dan Cox said, adding that the attacker then fled. 
</P>
<P>
The co-worker drove the van about a block back to the victim's house at 250 
Carriagedale Drive, where the victim died. 
</P>
<P>
Cox said the victim had just driven away from his home about 5:20 a.m. when the 
gunman appeared from the back of the van and fired at him. 
</P>
<P>
The motive for the attack was not immediately known and no suspects were in 
custody. 
</P>
</TEXT>
