<P>
An ABC television employee was shot and killed in the parking lot of a Los 
Feliz restaurant by a car burglar he tried to detain until police could arrive, 
authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Wayne Gibbs, 58, of Los Angeles was leaving a McDonald's restaurant at Sunset 
Boulevard and Fountain Avenue about 8 p.m. Thursday when he came upon a man 
breaking into his car, Detective Sam Jacobellis said. 
</P>
<P>
Gibbs was shot when he tried to hold the suspect until police could be 
summoned, Jacobellis said. 
</P>
<P>
He was taken to Hollywood Presbyterian Medical Center, where he died a short 
time later. 
</P>
<P>
Gibbs was an employee at the nearby ABC Television Center, where he had worked 
as a field engineer for 40 years, Jacobellis said. The ABC studios are located 
less than a mile from the shooting site. 
