ASHKENAZY ON TAPE AT CRYSTAL CATHEDRAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A special Mother's Day worship service featuring a taped performance by 
renowned pianist Vladimir Ashkenazy will take place at 9 and 11 a.m. Sunday at 
Garden Grove's Crystal Cathedral. 
</P>
<P>
Ashkenazy's recital was taped in the 3,000-seat cathedral on May 3 before his 
performance at the Dorothy Chandler Pavilion. He gave a private recital of 
Brahms' Rhapsody in E flat, Opus 119, according to Colleen Johnson, assistant 
program director at Crystal Cathedral. 
</P>
<P>
"Dr. Schuller happens to know him (Ashkenazy) personally and asked him to come 
perform and he did," Johnson explained. 
